The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 December is 124,584 (14,359 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 December, there were 5,411 new confirmed cases (623.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 December, there were 5,722 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 5% (311 fewer cases).
